HEADWORD: Stereotypery
<hw>Ste"re*o*ty`per*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The art, process, or employment of making stereotype
plates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where stereotype plates are made; a
stereotype foundry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stereotypic</ent>⟦br⟧
